For Singapore, it was no better,

192
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:45,080
as 2016 marked a seven-year high

193
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,600
for the number of workers laid off.

194
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,960
Here’s Jojo Joget with the story.

195
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:56,280
37-year-old IT manager, Roland Seow,

196
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,560
had planned to quit his job
in December.

197
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,520
But one morning in October,

198
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,560
as he stepped into his office,

199
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,840
Seow was asked to go
to a senior manager’s office

200
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,120
for an urgent meeting.

201
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,440
It was there that he learnt

202
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,480
that he was being retrenched.

203
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:13,520
<i>Huat ah!</i>

204
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,440
If I had resigned in December,

205
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:18,400
I would not have qualified
for my year-end bonus.

206
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:21,200
But because they decided to sack me,

207
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,760
now they have to pay me
eight months severance pay,

208
00:10:23,760 --> 00:10:26,720
one month pay for each year
I served in the company.

209
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:29,440
So after I clear off all my
credit-card debt,

210
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,800
I finally, can have a staycation,

211
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,360
at Hotel 81.

212
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,640
<i>Huat ah!</i>

213
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:40,800
According to numbers released
by the government,

214
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,960
the number of layoffs hit
a seven-year high

215
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:46,880
in the first nine months of 2016 alone.

216
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:51,000
With economic prospects
looking bleak on the horizon,

217
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,880
more people are expected

218
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:55,280
to be retrenched in the coming months.

219
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:56,960
Die!

220
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,280
Sore throat ah, sore throat.

221
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,400
Do you have honey?

222
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,200
Honey plus Tongkat Ali.

223
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:07,120
Can, ah.

224
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,120
I sound like a frog.

225
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:13,080
Actually, the Singapore
economy is in deep...

226
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,160
trouble, I tell you.

227
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,920
You know how I know?

228
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:19,280
Because my esteemed colleagues
told me so.

229
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,320
The problem with Singaporeans

230
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:25,160
is that they know how
to get from 0 to 80.

231
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:29,240
But they have no idea
how to get from 80 to 100.

232
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:31,720
And that is where
you earn your money.

233
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,160
Actually who wrote this
statement, ah?

234
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,840
Can explain to me what
it means, or not?

235
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,640
Still rolling?

236
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:46,080
I don’t know about 80 to 100...all that.

237
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:48,000
All I know is...

238
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,680
life is very stressful.

239
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:53,880
You know,

240
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:56,160
every time I come into the office,

241
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,960
I have to look over my shoulder
to see whether

242
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,880
my boss is coming to retrench me.

243
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,800
Last time,

244
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:08,880
I only had to worry whether
he was coming to harass me.

245
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,960
Human-resource experts say

246
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:21,080
retrenchments,
although painful for workers,

247
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,400
affects employers greatly too.

248
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,800
Whenever they talk about retrenchment,

249
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:28,480
they always blame it on the employers.

250
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,720
But what can we do?

251
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,680
If I don’t take this drastic action,

252
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,720
I tell you, my business
will bungkus (pack).

253
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,560
I think the last few months
already bungkus (pack).

254
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,560
Not like the nasi lemak,
which is very nice,

255
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:42,360
but this bungkus (pack) is very horrible.

256
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,560
Just two days ago,

257
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:48,240
I retrenched another 25 of my workers,

258
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:49,800
so 25 plus…

259
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,600
I know it feels a bit lonely,

260
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,520
but on the bright side,

261
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:59,000
I get to save cost on this corner,

262
